icon|USA}} [[Hartford Whalers]] || -\n|-align=\"center\"\n|! style=\"text-align:center; \"background:#00008b; color:#FFFFFF;\"|December 27, 1989 || [[Krylya Sovetov Moscow]] {{flagicon|URS}} || 3\u20134 (OT) || {{flagicon|USA}} '''Hartford Whalers''' || -\n|-align=\"center\"\n|! style=\"text-align:center; \"background:#00008b; color:#FFFFFF;\"|January 3, 1991 || [[HC Dynamo Moscow|Dynamo Moscow]] {{flagicon|URS}} || 0-0 || {{flagicon|USA}} Hartford Whalers || -\n|-align=\"center\"\n|! style=\"text-align:center; \"background:#00008b; color:#FFFFFF;\"|December 14, 2019 || {{ihw-rt|CAN}} || 1-4 || '''{{ihw|USA}}''' || 7,126 <ref>https://www.courant.com/sports/hc-sp-womens-hockey-usa-canada-rivalry-series-1215-20191215-55y45lo5knbttjoi2roimdaudi-story.html</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n===UConn Huskies===\nThe XL Center serves as the second home for the University of Connecticut's men's and women's basketball programs. At the start of the 2014\u201315 season the UConn men's ice hockey program moved to the XL Center as a condition of its joining Hockey East.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/college-sports/story/_/id/8082157/connecticut-huskies-accept-membership-hockey-east|title=Connecticut joins Hockey East|publisher=Associated Press|accessdate=February 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====UConn Hockey Attendance Records====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- \n! style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|UConn Huskies|color=white}};\" | Date\n! style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|UConn Huskies|color=white}};\" | Opponent\n! style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|UConn Huskies|color=white}};\" | Result\n! style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|UConn Huskies|color=white}};\" | Attendance\n|-\n| February 9, 2019 ||[[Merrimack Warriors men's ice hockey|Merrimack]] || '''W''' 5-0 || 8,211<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uconnhuskies.com/news/2019/2/9/mens-ice-hockey-evans-scores-twice-as-huskies-shutout-merrimack-5-0.aspx|title=Evans Scores Twice as Huskies Shutout Merrimack, 5-0|publisher=UConn Huskies|accessdate=February 10, 2019}}</ref>