ory residential tower named Hartford 21 which opened in 2006 and is the tallest residential tower between New York City and Boston.\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Connecticut}}\n*[[List of convention centers in the United States]]\n*[[List of NCAA Division I basketball arenas]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[http://www.xlcenter.com/ XL Center]\n\n{{S-start-collapsible|header={{S-sta|et}}}}\n{{Succession box\n | title = Home of the [[Hartford Whalers|New England / Hartford Whalers]]\n | years = 1974\u20131978<br>1980\u20131997\n | before = [[Boston Garden]]<br>[[MassMutual Center|Springfield Civic Center]]\n | after = [[MassMutual Center|Springfield Civic Center]]<br>[[Greensboro Coliseum]]\n}}\n{{Succession box\n | title = Home of the New England Sea Wolves\n | years = 1999\u20132000\n | before = [[Madison Square Garden]]\n | after = [[Scotiabank Arena|Air Canada Centre]]\n}}\n{{Succession box\n | title = Host of [[NHL All-Star Game]]\n | years = 1986\n | before = [[Scotiabank Saddledome|Olympic Saddledome]]\n | after = [[St. Louis Arena]]\n}}\n{{Succession box\n | title = Home of the [[Hartford Wolf Pack]]/Connecticut Whale\n | years = 1997-Present\n | before = [[Broome County Veterans Memorial Arena]]\n | after = Current Arena\n}}\n{{Succession box\n | title = Host of [[WrestleMania]]\n | years = [[WrestleMania XI|1995]]\n | before = [[Madison Square Garden]]\n | after = [[Honda Center|Arrowhead Pond of Anaheim]]\n}}\n{{end}}\n\n{{University of Connecticut}}\n{{UConn Huskies men's basketball navbox}}\n{{UConn Huskies women's basketball navbox}}\n{{UConn Huskies men's ice hockey navbox}}\n{{Boston Celtics}}\n{{Hartford Whalers}}\n{{Hartford Wolf Pack}}\n{{Connecticut Coyotes}}\n{{Toronto Phantoms}}\n{{AHL Arenas}}\n{{Hockey East}}\n{{American Athletic Conference basketball venue navbox}}\n{{WorldCupofHockey}}\n{{Music venues of Connecticut}}\n{{Hartford, Connecticut}}\n{{Connecticut NCAA Division I college basketball venue 